<item>
            <title>[SOLR-16406] Module loading does not work when using SOLR_MODULES in solr.in.sh</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-16406</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As documented there are several ways to enable Solr modules.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When using -Dsolr.modules=analysis-extras all works as expected and the start up produces following log:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
2022-09-09T12:31:41.911492838Z 2022-09-09 12:31:41.910 INFO &#160;(main) [] o.a.s.c.SolrResourceLoader Added 12 libs to classloader, from paths: [/opt/solr/modules/analysis-extras/lib]
2022-09-09T12:31:41.911590590Z 2022-09-09 12:31:41.911 INFO &#160;(main) [] o.a.s.c.NodeConfig Added module analysis-extras. libPath=/opt/solr/modules/analysis-extras/lib with 12 libs &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;But when using SOLR_MODULES=analysis-extras in solr.in.sh the module is not loaded.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Additionally i checked the `solr` (under /opt/bin/solr) script itself and /opt/solr/bin/solr.in.sh is included&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
